message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE. The paper deals with convolutional neural networks applied to 3D objects, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the issue of preserving meaningful representations of objects under transformations, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper introduces a new type of network architecture, which could be considered a contribution to the field of graph theory (cs.GR). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the network on classification and segmentation tasks, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE).
